This paper deals with the problem of anomaly detection in keystroke biometrics, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses various machine learning techniques used for anomaly detection, such as auto-encoding neural networks and ensemble methods, which are commonly used in the fields of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and information retrieval (cs.IR). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
